hpnicfVoiceInterface.name: hpnicfVoiceInterface

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

hpnicfVoiceInterface.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of the voice interface general configuration.

hpnicfVoiceIfConfigTable.name: hpnicfVoiceIfConfigTable
hpnicfVoiceIfConfigTable.description: The table contains configurable parameters for both analog voice interface and digital voice interface.

hpnicfVoiceIfConfigEntry.name: hpnicfVoiceIfConfigEntry
hpnicfVoiceIfConfigEntry.description: The entry of voice interface table.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgCngOn.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgCngOn
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgCngOn.description: This object indicates whether the silence gaps should be filled with background noise. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgNonLinearSwitch.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgNonLinearSwitch
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgNonLinearSwitch.description: This object expresses the nonlinear processing is enable or disable for the voice interface. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line. Currently, only digital voice subscriber lines can be set disabled.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgInputGain.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgInputGain
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgInputGain.description: This object indicates the amount of gain added to the receiver side of the voice interface. Unit is 0.1 db. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgOutputGain.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgOutputGain
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgOutputGain.description: This object indicates the amount of gain added to the send side of the voice interface. Unit is 0.1 db. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch.description: This object indicates whether the echo cancellation is enabled. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelDelay.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelDelay
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelDelay.description: This object indicates the delay of the echo cancellation for the voice interface. This value couldn't be modified unless hpnicfVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch is enable. Unit is milliseconds. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line. The default value of this object is 32.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgTimerDialInterval.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgTimerDialInterval
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgTimerDialInterval.description: The interval, in seconds, between two dialing numbers. The default value of this object is 10 seconds. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 with loop-start or ground-start protocol voice subscriber line.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgTimerFirstDial.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgTimerFirstDial
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgTimerFirstDial.description: The period of time, in seconds, before dialing the first number. The default value of this object is 10 seconds. It is applicable to FXO, FXS subscriber lines and E1/T1 with loop-start or ground-start protocol voice subscriber line.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgPrivateline.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgPrivateline
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgPrivateline.description: This object indicates the E.164 phone number for plar mode. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hpnicfVoiceIfCfgRegTone.name: hpnicfVoiceIfCfgRegTone
hpnicfVoiceIfCfgRegTone.description: This object uses 2 or 3 letter country code specify voice parameters of different countrys. This value will take effect on all voice interfaces of all cards on the device.
